Types of attacks and threats are as follows:
1. Malware
   - Viruses
    -Worms
    -Trojans
2. Phishing
   - Email phishing
   - Spear phishing
   - Whaling
3. Denial of Service (DoS) and Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) Attacks
   - Network flooding
   - Application layer attacks

4. Man-in-the-Middle (MitM) Attacks
   - Eavesdropping
   - Session hijacking
   - HTTPS spoofing

5. SQL Injection
   - Database manipulation
   - Unauthorized data retrieval

6. Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
   - Stored XSS
   - Reflected XSS
   - DOM-based XSS

7. Password Attacks
   - Brute force attacks
   - Dictionary attack
8. Advanced Persistent Threats (APTs)
   - Long-term infiltration
   - Data exfiltration

9. Insider Threats
   - Data theft
   - Sabotage

10. Zero-Day Exploits
    - Exploiting unknown vulnerabilities

11. Drive-by Downloads
    - Malicious software download without user's knowledge

12. IoT Attacks
    - Device hijacking
    - Botnet attacks

